        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 11:46PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 1146 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 23
miles east of White Sulphur Springs, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Martinsdale and Lennep.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
